  "texts": [
    "Users can launch a smart contract by sending a transaction to the contract address.",
    "When certain events take place, they transfer cryptocurrency automatically.Smart contract code, in contrast to standard computer code, is deposited in a blockchain network, run, and its outcomes are validated by nodes taking part in the blockchain network.",
    "By posting a transaction on the blockchain, any user can form a contract.",
    "When a message or other contract is received from a user, the smart contract's program code will be performed and cannot be modified after it has been generated.",
    "Smart contracts execute a specific piece of their code when triggered by a user via a custom message or an action from another smart contract."
  ],
